review_comments.body:
``` java
        if(containerCapStr.equals("")) {
            this.containerCap = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        } else {
            this.containerCap = Integer.parseInt(containerCapStr);
        }
```

I found this in DockerCloud.java. If zero, then this Cloud will not be used. So "The maximum number of containers that this provider is allowed to run" is correct for Integer.MAX_VALUE and also 0.

I think this could be a bug. What happens, if the numer is below zero?

I found this:

``` java
        if (instanceCapStr.equals("")) {
            this.instanceCap = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        } else {
            this.instanceCap = Integer.parseInt(instanceCapStr);
        }
```

The description above is wrong. In my opionion if it's 0 it should not start Instances on this machine. If it's blank, then it's Integer.MAX_VALUE.

